scanmark.description: Works that are excessively watermarked by translator/scanner and are subject to replacement by non-watermarked versions.

screenshots.description: Screenshots taken from a movie, [h-]anime, or television show.
screenshots.note: Images that are animated do not qualify.

stereoscopic.description: A  pair of stereo images which can be viewed using a stereoscope.
stereoscopic.note: Should not be confused with the 3d or anaglyph tags.

story arc.description: A story spawning multiple chapters within a single gallery.
story arc.note:
Requires a minimum of ~75 pages or 4 chapters, whichever comes first. For tankoubons 50%+ of the content is required to qualify.
Should not be confused with multi-work series.

tankoubon.description: A complete book by a single artist published by a third party. Primarily only in the Manga or Non-H categories.
tankoubon.note: Incomplete tankoubons (e.g. individual chapters) do not qualify.

themeless.description: An unorganized gallery with no common artist, parody, character, story, motif, or other focus.

Do not use outside of the Imageset, Non-H, Cosplay, Misc, or Western categories.

time stop.description: Time stops for at least one character while another takes sexual advantage of the situation. Also includes any time alterations done for the same reason.

uncensored.description: Either published uncensored or later decensored, the gallery is not censored at any point.
uncensored.note: Should not be used on galleries located in the  Western category.

variant set.description: A gallery depicting only a single scenery from a static perspective.
variant set.note: Covers, colophons, etc. do not disqualify.

watermarked.note: Should NOT be used for any works that have watermarks, only those that are being expunged immediately as part of the linked expunge reason. See the scanmark tag for works that are to be replaced.

webtoon.description: Any webcomic published online. Typically formatted in a vertical layout, utilizing whitespace instead of paneling.
webtoon.note: Country of origin does not matter, only the format.

western cg.description: A digital pornographic set of western origin without panels. Typically in color, less hand-drawn, and with more detailed backgrounds. Must depict a sequence of events or be sold / distributed as a whole. Also acceptable for frames extracted from western erotic games.
western cg.note:
For the Western category only. Western 3D sets do not qualify.
Designated as a future category tag candidate.

western imageset.description: Drawn content of Western origin that does not constitute a comic or cg set (e.g. loose images, screenshots, etc.) Images within such galleries are preferred to have a singular theme (e.g. singular artist, series, character, or fetish).
western imageset.note:
For the Western category only. Non-pornographic galleries do not qualify.
Designated as a future category tag candidate.

western non-h.description: Western origin drawings that are NOT pornographic in nature (a single explicit image featuring sex automatically disqualifies a gallery). Small amounts of nudity are permitted if they are non-sexual in nature (e.g. nipple slips).
western non-h.note:
For the misc category only. 
Designated as a future category tag candidate.
